projects.name: Sentiment Analysis Of Product Reviews
projects.description: Spearheaded the creation of a comprehensive sentiment analysis platform capable of handling varied sentiments and expressions found in project reviews. The platform includes features for sentiment categorization, trend analysis, and real-time updates. Implemented Selenium to create an instance of Chrome in order to interact with the correct elements of the web page. Employed user-friendly design principles to ensure a seamless and intuitive user experience for interacting with the sentiment analysis platform. This included user interfaces that facilitate easy input of project review data and visualization tools for clear presentation of sentiment insights. Integrating cutting-edge data analysis methodologies with industry-standard Python libraries such as Pandas, the model correlates sentiment data with review counts.

projects.name: Utility Hub
projects.description: Utility Hub is a pioneering Android app created using Kotlin, XML, HTML, and CSS within Android Studio. It seamlessly integrates multiple e-commerce platforms through custom APIs, offering users a unified shopping experience. This project demonstrates proficiency in mobile app development, API integration, and user-centric design.
